{
  "text": "If \u03c9 is a moderate weight on R d , then there exists a submultiplicative weight v on R d such that (1.5) and (1.6) hold, cf. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Moreover if v is submultiplicative on R d , then For a given k \u2208 N, we let P E (R d 0 +\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7+d k ) be the set of all moderate weights on R d 0 +\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7+d k , and P(R d 0 +\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7+d k ) be the subset of P E (R d 0 +\u00b7\u00b7\u00b7+d k ) which consists of weights of polynomial type.",
